5
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,000
So, let's get right into it.

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:32,000
We are over here in the program, and we can see right away that I have put something into this box here.

7
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:38,000
It is giving us a height and width designation, just a very simple one.

8
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:50,000
That gives us the largest width and height that we could possibly use, and it is shown inside of that large rectangle there with the large letter 'B'.

9
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:07,000
The first step that we need to do so that we can trace our custom button is that we are needing to drag an image from the file system directly onto this area where it has the large letter 'B'.

10
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:12,000
We are now going to drag over our image from the file system over here, and to where we see the letter 'B'.

11
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:20,000
We are now going to drag over our image from the file system over here, and to where we see the letter 'B'.

12
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:23,000
And there we have it and it shows up there on the screen.

13
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,000
The problem we can see is that it seems too small.

14
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
What should we do?

15
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:37,000
We must move our mouse cursor over top of that region with the large letter 'B' and we can then scroll with the mousewheel. Now we see that something interesting is happening.

16
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:45,000
We are able to adjust the scale of on screen guide.

17
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:54,000
When we scroll down to 4, 3, 2, and 1, we see that there is a special upscaling factor applied.

18
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:58,000
I built that in to the program for the purpose of pixel art.

19
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:03,000
So that when you bring the buttons back into the program they will be scaled up in size.

20
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:07,000
They will not be the size that you see while you are drawing them.

21
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:16,000
So, you can draw them at that small pixel size and then you can bring them into the program and they will suddenly become larger.

22
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Because of that reason, you are getting a really good economy on the size of your image and your buttons.

23
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:31,000
So, your button is not too expensive in terms of how much it costs for tranfering it through the internet.

24
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:41,000
So there we have it. This one here has 180 units of height and 100 units of width, but it's not particularly useful to us at the moment.

25
