00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Let's open it up in MS Paint and see what it really looks like.

36
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:04,000
So, this is a shape key which had some definition given with the 'h' and 'w' syntax.

37
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:15,000
The important part is not that this shape key is useful graphical image right now. It isn't.

38
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:26,000
The entire purpose of the shape key is to have a nice picture in your file system, allowing you to visually identify the shape key.

39
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,000
That is the whole reason that it is there.

40
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Now I will show how to use it.

41
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Once you have produced a shape key by saving one using the syntax. (The shape keys are not mandatory.)

42
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:41,000
You can ignore them.

43
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:52,000
The shape key has a special syntax plainly visible in the file name.

44
00:04:52,000 --> 00:05:17,000
Now I will describe the syntax. It uses the 'h' and 'w' syntax.

45
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:27,000
This describes rows of rectangles which share the same height.

46
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Just be sure not to remove this syntax from the end of your file name if you wish to rename the file.

47
00:05:51,000 --> 00:06:02,000
The nice thing about this is that you can simply drag this thing directly onto one of the letters, and it will be installed in that location.

48
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:06,000
I am choosing the letter 'n'.

49
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:10,000
The letter 'n' now contains the information for that shape key.

50
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:23,000
Then we use the scroll wheel a bit and we see that all of this defined shape key has been drawn in for us.

51
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:32,000
 I have made this one in advance, and so I can then easily show you that this lines up perfectly with the drawing.

52
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:45,000
But, just briefly I will go through the process to demonstrate tracing.

53
00:06:45,000 --> 00:07:01,000
We will manually enter the syntax. I will use period and hyphen on the number pad, but, you can also use the letters 'h' and 'w'.

54
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,000
To begin, we will pick the first two numbers: 'h10w10'.

55
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:08,000
This is just so that we have something to look at as a starting point.

56
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:37,000
Now we can adjust and add 'w' to get more widths.

57
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:45,000
So, we have the definitions and have successfully traced the first four letters.

58
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:51,000
I have already traced this out in advance, so let's just move along.

59
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:55,000
So, here it is completed.

