You must then drag that file back on to the program screen.

65
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:35,000
I will show you this soon, but first I will tell about the syntax of the file which has just now been saved.

66
00:08:35,000 --> 00:09:11,000
We can see that we have the same syntax that was stored in the shape key. (file name prefix 'TEMPL')

67
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:13,000
So, let's see what we can do.

68
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:19,000
We use escape so that we have a nice blank screen.

69
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:25,000
I will next drag this template back into the program.

70
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:37,000
This might seem tricky, but it isn't.

71
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:47,000
If we want buttons, we must now choose between 6, 4, or 2.

72
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:52,000
This is not the number of buttons but, rather, it is the number of button states which will be used.

73
00:09:52,000 --> 00:10:12,000
When we hover with the mouse over the button, this is the hover state.

74
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:15,000
When we click down, this is the active state.

75
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,000
And when the button clicked, it then gets the focused state.

76
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:24,000
We have the choice of doing all 6, which gives only 5 useable states.

77
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:31,000
We prefer to use either 4, which is ideal for desktop computers or 2 which is enough for mobile telephones.

78
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:35,000
I will now give a brief description assuming 4 button states are used.

79
00:10:35,000 --> 00:11:01,000
base

80
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,000
focus

81
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,000
hover

82
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,000
active

83
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:27,000
That is very important to know about if you are not familiar with HTML.

84
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:32,000
Let's now continue with our process.

