103
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:38,000
We can now see that our buttons function properly, and look exactly like the graphics that we drew.

104
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:45,000
This file that we have produced can be used and reused at any time.

105
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:51,000
We have a very nice, persistent, templating system in place.

106
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,000
The system is comprised of: A shape key (file name prefix 'SHAPE');

107
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:59,000
A first template, which gets a single image (file name prefix 'TEMPL');

108
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:08,000
and the finished button set (file name prefix 'READY').

109
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:15,000
We can even copy this finished button in our file system and make some kind of alternate imagery, and it would still work.

